Package game.common

Interface Field

All Known Implementing Classes:
EndField, PathField, StartField, WallField
public interface Field
Common interface for all field types that are in maze.

  • Method Details

    • canMove

      boolean canMove()
      Determines if any FieldObject could move to this field (aka it's not wall or something similar).
      Returns:
      True if any FieldObject can move here, false otherwise.

    • getAll

      Iterable<FieldObject> getAll()
      Returns an iterable list of all FieldObjects on this field. The order has to be respected for rendering. Throws an UnsupportedOperationException when FieldObject can not be put in this field. Use canMove() to determine if object can be put in this field.
      Returns:
      Iterable of all FieldObjects on this field.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Determines if this field is empty of FieldObjects.
      Returns:
      True if there are no MazeObjects, false otherwise.

    • nextField

      Field nextField(Field.Direction dir)
      Returns neighboring field in the dir Field.Direction.
      Parameters:
      dir - Direction.
      Returns:
      Neighboring field in the dir Field.Direction.

    • put

      boolean put(FieldObject object)
      Puts FieldObject into this field. Throws an UnsupportedOperationException when FieldObject can not be put in this field. Use canMove() to determine if object can be put in this field.
      Parameters:
      object - Object to put in.
      Returns:
      True if successful, false otherwise.

    • remove

      boolean remove(FieldObject object)
      Removes FieldObject from this field. Throws an UnsupportedOperationException when FieldObject can not be put in this field. Use canMove() to determine if object can be put in this field.
      Parameters:
      object - Object to remove from this field.
      Returns:
      True if successful, false otherwise.

    • setMaze

      void setMaze(Maze maze)
      Sets a reference to Maze.
      Parameters:
      maze - maze to set the reference to.

    • getLast

      FieldObject getLast()
      Returns last/newest FieldObjects on this field. Throws an UnsupportedOperationException when FieldObject can not be put in this field. Use canMove() to determine if object can be put in this field.
      Returns:
      Iterable of all FieldObjects on this field.

      Returns:
